data.name: cbActorTemplate.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Select an actor template to verify against. During export the actor must, at a minimum, contain the components listed in the template or the export will fail.
If no template is selected, the actor will not be checked.

data.name: btnCreateActorNode.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Actors are created from smaller building blocks called Scene Nodes. This drop down contains the Scene Nodes available for constructing Actors.
Build an Actor by adding Scene Nodes from this list. An actor may contain any number and/or type of Scene Node.

data.name: btnAttachActorController.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Controllers are attached to Scene Nodes to influence them in some way. The influence is dependent upon the type of controller.
For example, an animation controller will animate the Scene Nodes it is attached to. To add a controller, select a scene node from the Scene Explorer then choose a controller.

data.name: btnAddPostEffect.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Post Effects are applied to a camera's viewport after all geometry has been rendered. To apply a post effect, select a camera from the Scene Explorer and then choose a post effect.
Post effects can be layered on the same camera. They are order dependent.

data.name: btnUseLights.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Choose the lighting mode in which to view the actor inside the viewport. There are 3 modes.
Default Lights - this is standard white lighting used to shade geometry from the viewpoint of the camera
Scene Lights - only lights added to the scene will be used to illuminate geometry
Scenario Lights - predefined light layouts that are useful for visualizing geometry

data.name: btnActionExplorer.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Show/Hide Action Explorer window.
The Action Explorer allows you to exectute pre-defined actions on Scene Node. For example, you can play, pause, and mix the animation tracks of an Animation Controller.

data.name: btnWindowLibraryExplorer.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Show/Hide Library Explorer window.
The Library Explorer contains various libraries such as the Actor Library, Material Library, Controller Library, Texture Library and Audio Library. Each library allows you to inspect the assets and perform operations on them.

data.name: btnWindowOutputExplorer.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Show/Hide Output Explorer window.
The Output Explorer contains an event message log that provides useful debugging information during the use of XVP Designer. It also contains a command console connected to the target device.

data.name: btnWindowGraphExplorer.SuperTooltip
data.value:
Show/Hide Graph Explorer window.
The Graph Explorer allows you to explore and modify state machines in a visual manner. State machines can be built by creating nodes and connecting them via transitions.

data.name: ribtabWorkspace.SuperTooltip
data.value:
This tab allows you to create and manage Workspaces. Workspaces contain settings and preferences for a particular working environment.
For example, the target platform, network settings, and other information needed to work with XVP for a given project are specified here. The help system is also avaliable from this tab.

data.name: ribtabActorStudio.SuperTooltip
data.value:
This tab allows you to create and manage Actors. Actors are game entities built from smaller building blocks called Scene Nodes. Using the tools provided on this tab, you can construct new actors, edit properties for the actors and specifiy shading parameters.
You can also manage Actor Templates. Actor Templates provide a "contract" for an actor's layout. This ensures data exported from XVP Designer can be read properly by the runtime.

data.name: ribtabStageStudio.SuperTooltip
data.value:
This tab allows you to create Stages. Stages are groups of actor instances that have been previously created in Actor Studio. The tools on this tab allow you to create instances of Actors, place them in the world and edit their instanced properties.
Stage Templates can also be created and managed from this tab. Stage Templates define what type and how many actors should exist. The template ensure that Stages ae exported with all the Actors expected by the runtime.
